Package: tcp-splice
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Cong Wang <cwang@multikernel.io>
Section: net
Priority: optional
@DEPENDS@
Description: TCP loopback splice (co-located TCP acceleration)
 Accelerates co-located TCP - loopback and same-host container sidecars - by
 splicing two locally-connected TCP sockets through an in-kernel ring,
 bypassing the skb/softirq/TCP-receive path while leaving the real TCP
 connection intact.
 .
 This package ships a prebuilt kernel module for kernel @KVER@ (it refuses to
 load on any other kernel via vermagic), the tcp-splice-ctl control tool, and a
 systemd service that loads the module and applies the policy in
 /etc/tcp-splice/config.
